  chapters:
  - verses:
    - title: 
      content: 'This is the message[COMMENT[0]] that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        gave to Israel through the prophet Malachi.[COMMENT[1]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '1:1a '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: 'An Oracle: The message.'
      - number: '1:1b '
        contents:
        - ft: 
          body: 'Malachi '
        - ft: "means \u201Cmy messenger.\u201D"
          body: 
    - title: "\u2019s Love for Israel"
      content: "\u201CI have always loved you,\u201D says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t.\n\tBut
        you retort, \u201CReally? How have you loved us?\u201D\n\tAnd the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        replies, \u201CThis is how I showed my love for you: I loved your ancestor
        Jacob, "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "but I rejected his brother, Esau, and devastated his hill country.
        I turned Esau\u2019s inheritance into a desert for jackals.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Esau\u2019s descendants in Edom may say, \u201CWe have been shattered,
        but we will rebuild the ruins.\u201D\n\tBut the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        of Heaven\u2019s Armies replies, \u201CThey may try to rebuild, but I will
        demolish them again. Their country will be known as \u2018The Land of Wickedness,\u2019
        and their people will be called \u2018The People with Whom the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        Is Forever Angry.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "When you see the destruction for yourselves, you will say, \u2018Truly,
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t\u2019s greatness reaches far beyond Israel\u2019s
        borders!\u2019\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: Unworthy Sacrifices
      content: "The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s Armies says to the
        priests: \u201CA son honors his father, and a servant respects his master.
        If I am your father and master, where are the honor and respect I deserve?
        You have shown contempt for my name!\n\t\u201CBut you ask, \u2018How have
        we ever shown contempt for your name?\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CYou have shown contempt by offering defiled sacrifices on my
        altar.\n\t\u201CThen you ask, \u2018How have we defiled the sacrifices?[COMMENT[0]]\u2019\n\t\u201CYou
        defile them by saying the altar of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> deserves
        no respect. "
      comments:
      - number: '1:7 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'As in Greek version; Hebrew reads '
          body: defiled you?
    - title: 
      content: "When you give blind animals as sacrifices, isn\u2019t that wrong?
        And isn\u2019t it wrong to offer animals that are crippled and diseased?
        Try giving gifts like that to your governor, and see how pleased he is!\u201D
        says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s Armies.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CGo ahead, beg God to be merciful to you! But when you bring
        that kind of offering, why should he show you any favor at all?\u201D asks
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s Armies.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CHow I wish one of you would shut the Temple doors so that these
        worthless sacrifices could not be offered! I am not pleased with you,\u201D
        says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s Armies, \u201Cand I
        will not accept your offerings. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But my name is honored[COMMENT[0]] by people of other nations from
        morning till night. All around the world they offer[COMMENT[1]] sweet incense
        and pure offerings in honor of my name. For my name is great among the nations,\u201D
        says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s Armies.  "
      comments:
      - number: '1:11a '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Or '
          body: will be honored.
      - number: '1:11b '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Or '
          body: will offer.
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CBut you dishonor my name with your actions. By bringing contemptible
        food, you are saying it\u2019s all right to defile the Lord\u2019s table. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "You say, \u2018It\u2019s too hard to serve the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t,\u2019
        and you turn up your noses at my commands,\u201D says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        of Heaven\u2019s Armies. \u201CThink of it! Animals that are stolen and crippled
        and sick are being presented as offerings! Should I accept from you such
        offerings as these?\u201D asks the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CCursed is the cheat who promises to give a fine ram from his
        flock but then sacrifices a defective one to the Lord. For I am a great king,\u201D
        says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s Armies, \u201Cand my
        name is feared among the nations!"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: A Warning to the Priests
      content: "\u201CListen, you priests\u2014this command is for you! "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Listen to me and make up your minds to honor my name,\u201D says
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s Armies, \u201Cor I will
        bring a terrible curse against you. I will curse even the blessings you receive.
        Indeed, I have already cursed them, because you have not taken my warning
        to heart. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I will punish your descendants and splatter your faces with the manure
        from your festival sacrifices, and I will throw you on the manure pile. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then at last you will know it was I who sent you this warning so
        that my covenant with the Levites can continue,\u201D says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        of Heaven\u2019s Armies.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CThe purpose of my covenant with the Levites was to bring life
        and peace, and that is what I gave them. This required reverence from them,
        and they greatly revered me and stood in awe of my name. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They passed on to the people the truth of the instructions they received
        from me. They did not lie or cheat; they walked with me, living good and
        righteous lives, and they turned many from lives of sin.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CThe words of a priest\u2019s lips should preserve knowledge
        of God, and people should go to him for instruction, for the priest is the
        messenger of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s Armies. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But you priests have left God\u2019s paths. Your instructions have
        caused many to stumble into sin. You have corrupted the covenant I made with
        the Levites,\u201D says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s
        Armies. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CSo I have made you despised and humiliated in the eyes of all
        the people. For you have not obeyed me but have shown favoritism in the way
        you carry out my instructions.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: A Call to Faithfulness
      content: 'Are we not all children of the same Father? Are we not all created
        by the same God? Then why do we betray each other, violating the covenant
        of our ancestors?  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Judah has been unfaithful, and a detestable thing has been done in
        Israel and in Jerusalem. The men of Judah have defiled the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t\u2019s
        beloved sanctuary by marrying women who worship idols. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "May the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> cut off from the nation of Israel[COMMENT[0]]
        every last man who has done this and yet brings an offering to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        of Heaven\u2019s Armies.  "
      comments:
      - number: '2:12 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: 'from the tents of Jacob. '
        - ft: "The names \u201CJacob\u201D and \u201CIsrael\u201D are often interchanged
            throughout the Old Testament, referring sometimes to the individual patriarch
            and sometimes to the nation."
          body: 
    - title: 
      content: "Here is another thing you do. You cover the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t\u2019s
        altar with tears, weeping and groaning because he pays no attention to your
        offerings and doesn\u2019t accept them with pleasure. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "You cry out, \u201CWhy doesn\u2019t the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        accept my worship?\u201D I\u2019ll tell you why! Because the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        witnessed the vows you and your wife made when you were young. But you have
        been unfaithful to her, though she remained your faithful partner, the wife
        of your marriage vows.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Didn\u2019t the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> make you one with your
        wife? In body and spirit you are his.[COMMENT[0]] And what does he want?
        Godly children from your union. So guard your heart; remain loyal to the
        wife of your youth. "
      comments:
      - number: '2:15 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Or '
          body: "Didn\u2019t the one "
        - ft: 'or '
          body: "Didn\u2019t the one "
        - ft: The meaning of the Hebrew is uncertain.
          body: 
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CFor I hate divorce!\u201D[COMMENT[0]] says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t,
        the God of Israel. \u201CTo divorce your wife is to overwhelm her with cruelty,[COMMENT[1]]\u201D
        says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s Armies. \u201CSo guard
        your heart; do not be unfaithful to your wife.\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '2:16a '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: For he hates divorcing.
      - number: '2:16b '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: "to cover one\u2019s garment with violence."
    - title: 
      content: "You have wearied the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> with your words.\n\t\u201CHow
        have we wearied him?\u201D you ask.\n\tYou have wearied him by saying that
        all who do evil are good in the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t\u2019s sight,
        and he is pleased with them. You have wearied him by asking, \u201CWhere
        is the God of justice?\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: The Coming Day of Judgment
      content: "\u201CLook! I am sending my messenger, and he will prepare the way
        before me. Then the Lord you are seeking will suddenly come to his Temple.
        The messenger of the covenant, whom you look for so eagerly, is surely coming,\u201D
        says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s Armies.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CBut who will be able to endure it when he comes? Who will be
        able to stand and face him when he appears? For he will be like a blazing
        fire that refines metal, or like a strong soap that bleaches clothes. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "He will sit like a refiner of silver, burning away the dross. He
        will purify the Levites, refining them like gold and silver, so that they
        may once again offer acceptable sacrifices to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Then once more the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will accept the offerings
        brought to him by the people of Judah and Jerusalem, as he did in the past.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CAt that time I will put you on trial. I am eager to witness
        against all sorcerers and adulterers and liars. I will speak against those
        who cheat employees of their wages, who oppress widows and orphans, or who
        deprive the foreigners living among you of justice, for these people do not
        fear me,\u201D says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s Armies.  "
      comments: []
    - title: A Call to Repentance
      content: "\u201CI am the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t, and I do not change.
        That is why you descendants of Jacob are not already destroyed. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Ever since the days of your ancestors, you have scorned my decrees
        and failed to obey them. Now return to me, and I will return to you,\u201D
        says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s Armies.\n\t\u201CBut
        you ask, \u2018How can we return when we have never gone away?\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CShould people cheat God? Yet you have cheated me!\n\t\u201CBut
        you ask, \u2018What do you mean? When did we ever cheat you?\u2019\n\t\u201CYou
        have cheated me of the tithes and offerings due to me. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'You are under a curse, for your whole nation has been cheating me. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Bring all the tithes into the storehouse so there will be enough
        food in my Temple. If you do,\u201D says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        of Heaven\u2019s Armies, \u201CI will open the windows of heaven for you.
        I will pour out a blessing so great you won\u2019t have enough room to take
        it in! Try it! Put me to the test! "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Your crops will be abundant, for I will guard them from insects and
        disease.[COMMENT[0]] Your grapes will not fall from the vine before they
        are ripe,\u201D says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s Armies. "
      comments:
      - number: '3:11 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: from the devourer.
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CThen all nations will call you blessed, for your land will
        be such a delight,\u201D says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s
        Armies.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CYou have said terrible things about me,\u201D says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t.\n\t\u201CBut
        you say, \u2018What do you mean? What have we said against you?\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CYou have said, \u2018What\u2019s the use of serving God? What
        have we gained by obeying his commands or by trying to show the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        of Heaven\u2019s Armies that we are sorry for our sins? "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "From now on we will call the arrogant blessed. For those who do evil
        get rich, and those who dare God to punish them suffer no harm.\u2019\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: "\u2019s Promise of Mercy"
      content: 'Then those who feared the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> spoke with
        each other, and the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> listened to what they said.
        In his presence, a scroll of remembrance was written to record the names
        of those who feared him and always thought about the honor of his name.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CThey will be my people,\u201D says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        of Heaven\u2019s Armies. \u201COn the day when I act in judgment, they will
        be my own special treasure. I will spare them as a father spares an obedient
        child. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then you will again see the difference between the righteous and
        the wicked, between those who serve God and those who do not.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: The Coming Day of Judgment
      content: "  [COMMENT[1]]The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s Armies
        says, \u201CThe day of judgment is coming, burning like a furnace. On that
        day the arrogant and the wicked will be burned up like straw. They will be
        consumed\u2014roots, branches, and all.  "
      comments:
      - number: 
        contents:
        - ft: '  '
          body: 
      - number: '4:1 '
        contents:
        - ft: '  '
          body: 
        - ft: Verses 4:1-6 are numbered 3:19-24 in Hebrew text.
          body: 
        - ft: '  '
          body: 
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CBut for you who fear my name, the Sun of Righteousness will
        rise with healing in his wings.[COMMENT[0]] And you will go free, leaping
        with joy like calves let out to pasture. "
      comments:
      - number: '4:2 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Or '
          body: the sun of righteousness will rise with healing in its wings.
    - title: 
      content: "On the day when I act, you will tread upon the wicked as if they
        were dust under your feet,\u201D says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of
        Heaven\u2019s Armies.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CRemember to obey the Law of Moses, my servant\u2014all the
        decrees and regulations that I gave him on Mount Sinai[COMMENT[0]] for all
        Israel.  "
      comments:
      - number: '4:4 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: 'Horeb, '
        - ft: another name for Sinai.
          body: 
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CLook, I am sending you the prophet Elijah before the great
        and dreadful day of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> arrives. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "His preaching will turn the hearts of fathers to their children,
        and the hearts of children to their fathers. Otherwise I will come and strike
        the land with a curse.\u201D"
      comments: []
